article.headline: Kent St. 75, Akron 69
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Mike Scott and Chris Singletary each scored 18 points in Kent State's 75-69 win over Akron on Wednesday night. The Golden Flashes, who trailed 35-25 at halftime, got a layup from Singletary with 10:03 remaining to tie that game at 46-46. Rodriquez Sherman's layup 30 seconds later sparked a 15-8 run that gave Kent State a lead it never relinquished. Kent State shot 68 percent in the second half surge. Al Fisher scored 16 points and Haminn Quaintance added 12 for Kent State (15-4, 4-1 Mid-American). Nick Dials led Akron (14-4, 4-1) with 22 points. Jeremiah Wood had 14 and Brett McKnight added 10. Kent State shot 57.5 percent overall (23 of 40) and the Zips shot 44 percent (23 of 52).
